  <p>
    A loop in programming is a powerful way to automate repetitive tasks. In Evy, a loop is created
    using the <code>while</code> keyword.
  </p>
  <p>Here's the basic structure:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-evy">while loop_condition
    loop_body
    // â€¦
end</code></pre>
  <ul>
    <li><code>while</code>: Start of the loop.</li>
    <li><strong>loop_condition</strong>: As long as this condition is true, the loop repeats.</li>
    <li><strong>loop_body</strong>: Instructions to be repeated.</li>
    <li><code>end</code>: End of the loop.</li>
  </ul>
